== Installing ==

These instructions are tailored for Debian-like distros and specifically for
Trisquel 4.0.  Change as needed.


=== Installing to the system ===

$ sudo python3 ./setup.py install


=== Installing to your home directory ===

$ python3 ./setup.py install --user
$ echo "export PATH=$PATH:~/.local/bin" >> ~/.bashrc
$ source ~/.bashrc


=== Setting up a virtual environment ===

This option is preferred for development and only available if you have
downloaded the entire marionette git repository.

$ sudo apt-get install python-pip
$ pip install virtualenv
$ ./create-env.sh
$ source env/bin/activate
$ ./setup.py install
